{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C and grease a baking dish.","Place sausages in prepared dish and bake for 30-35 minutes (180°C), turning occasionally, until cooked. Meanwhile, make casserole.","Place garlic, onions and oil in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add bacon and sauté <nobr>5 min\/120°C\/\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add wine and, with simmering basket in place of measuring cup, cook <nobr>2 min\/Varoma\/\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add tomatoes, water, beef stock, sugar, tomato purée, Worcestershire sauce, thyme, mixed herbs, salt and pepper then, with simmering basket in place of measuring cup, cook <nobr>20 min\/110°C\/\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add beans and, with simmering basket in place of measuring cup, cook <nobr>10 min\/110°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Divide casserole between serving bowls and top each with 2 cooked sausages. Sprinkle with parsley (if using) then serve with crusty bread."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["12 pork sausages","3 garlic cloves","200 g onions, quartered","30 g olive oil, plus extra for greasing","150 g smoked bacon, cut in pieces (5 cm)","100 g red wine","400 g tinned chopped tomatoes","300 g water, boiling","1 beef stock cube (for 0.5 l), crumbled","1 Tbsp dark brown muscovado sugar","2 Tbsp tomato purée","2 Tbsp Worcestershire sauce","3 - 4 sprigs fresh thyme, leaves only, to taste","1 tsp dried mixed herbs","½ tsp fine sea salt","¼ tsp ground black pepper","480 g tinned cannellini beans, rinsed, drained (2 x 400 g tins)","fresh parsley leaves, for garnishing (optional)","crusty bread, for serving"]}],"id":"r301976","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-8g2gX80uWco\/XZQFivOphgI\/AAAAAAAAbz8\/Kcoi3QoaxisUIOAW-yUNB4H9FDIG3STMQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_6kvG49b8myMtXkqP.png","title":"Sausage and Bacon Casserole","publishedAt":"2018-12-03T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"26 g","fat":"40.5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"33.5 g","calories":"2606 kJ \/ 626 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking dish, oven","hintsAndTricks":["A hearty, warming casserole featuring a family favourite: sausages. The casserole is made whilst the sausages are cooking, then served all together alongside fresh, crusty bread. Much heartier than soup and a variation on sausage and mash, pop this on your weekly meal plan. You won’t regret it!"],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","50m","6 portions"]}